result.execSummary:
The defendant Austin D. Kuthe was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Austin D. Kuthe is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Austin D. Kuthe was found guilty of Possess Amphetamine/LSD/Psilocin, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(d).

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Austin D. Kuthe in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Andrew Christianson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Gumz states plea agreement to Ct. 1. Ct. 2 to be dismissed.  Atty Christianson does not object to expungment with conditions.
Court questions the defendant.  Defendant agrees and enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed.

Atty Christianson makes sentencing recommendations.
Atty Gumz makes sentencing arguments.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.

BY THE COURT:  Ct. 1:  Pay fine and costs = $442.00
Ct. 2 to be dismissed.
bond to be applied; balance to be returned to the party that posted it.

  If after 12 months the defendant has paid the fine and costs in full, has had no criminal violations or finishes all counseling or treatment that he is in, the defendant may petition the court for Expungement 973.015.
Return date on March 4, 2015 at 03:30 pm.

Attorney Mark Jay Gumz appeared by phone.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Atty. Gumz waived reading of complaint. Stand Mute. Court entered not guilty plea. Return date March 4, 2015 at 3:30 p.m. Bond continued
Initial appearance on January 26, 2015 at 11:00 am.
